  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0bae\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0b95\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba3 \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bca\u0b9f\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bae\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0baf\u0bcb\u0b9a\u0ba9\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0baa\u0bc6\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bca\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b85\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb5\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bae\u0bcd - \u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8 \u0baa\u0bca\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0baf\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1 \u0b86\u0ba3\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb4\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "It is essential to get the views of the people regarding the tariff revision - Public Utilities Commission of Sri Lanka",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "The proposals put forward by the Ceylon Electricity Board regarding the tariff revision have been fully considered.",
        "It is essential to get the aspirations and ideas of the general public regarding electricity tariff revision.",
        "Ideas related to the tariff increase proposed by the Ceylon Electricity Board will be published on the official website of the Public Utilities Commission of Sri Lanka www.pucsl.gov.lk from today.",
        "Janaka Ratnayake, Chairman of the Public Utilities Commission of Sri Lanka, said that the public can upload their ideas within 3 weeks.",
        "He was addressing a media briefing at the Public Utilities Commission of Sri Lanka on Monday (27).",
        "The Ceylon Electricity Board (CEB) has fully considered the idea of \u200b\u200brevising the electricity tariff to the current level as the cost of electricity has increased.",
        "The ideas put forward by the Electricity Board regarding the tariff revision will be made public through newspapers and social media today.",
        "The public can upload their ideas within 21 days on the official website of the Public Utilities Commission.",
        "The Commission has rejected the proposal of the Ceylon Electricity Board to increase the tariff for consumers using 30 to 60 units by 835 percent.",
        "The commission has urged the government to provide some relief schemes for low-income earners.",
        "It has been decided to revise the proposal put forward by the Electricity Board to fix the charge for a unit of electricity at 32 rupees and to fix it at 28 rupees.",
        "He said the commission was looking at revising electricity tariffs so that the public and the Electricity Board would not face a financial crisis in the current crisis."
      ],
